CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 6, 1946, pg. 25, reads: "Meet the Members of the Centre Avenue YMCA men's volleyball team who will make their initial appearance on Thursday at the Centre Avenue 'Y' gym at 7:30 pg. M. They will oppose the East Liberty YMCA in Metro YMCA Volleyball League.  The are, from left to right, seated: Stanford Howard, John Farrell, Cornell Cooper, Richard Martin, and W. C. Lane.  Back row, standing: Pomeroyal Fountain, physical director; James Johnson, Coach; Arbrie Bankston and H. S. Snead.  Missing from the picture are Max Thompson, Bert Wallace, John Brewer and James Atkins."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Centre Avenue YMCA volleyball team wearing "Pittsburgh" tee-shirts, seated from left: Stanford Howard, John Farrell, Cornell Cooper, Richard Martin, W. C. Lane; back row: Pomeroyal Fountain, James Johnson, Arbrie Bankston, and H. S. Snead
